Q: Delete distinct data A: <p><strong>Try this one</strong>   </p>

<pre><code>User::with('getAttendance')-&gt;distinct()-&gt;get();
</code></pre>

Q: Need to get records using day between from day and to day A: <p><strong>try this one</strong>    </p>

<pre><code>SELECT booking_times.* FROM booking_times WHERE DATE_FORMAT(booking_times.from_day, 'enter day') AND DATE_FORMAT(booking_times.to_day, 'enter to day');
</code></pre>

Q: PHP/Mysql &quot;Fatal error: Allowed memory size exhausted ..&quot; when trying to insert a big amount of data in chunks A: <p>Thanks to  Nigel Ren, who pointed out that I'm misusing try/catch construction</p>

<p>So instead of </p>

<pre><code>    .....
    try{
        $vendor_id = $vendors[$id];
    } catch (Exception $e) {
        continue;
    }
    ....
</code></pre>

<p>I'm using now</p>

<pre><code>$vendor_id = $vendors[$id]??null;
</code></pre>

<p>And no more memory leak problem. Don't know, why though, but now it works</p>
